      • getDiscussionDepth

        public int getDiscussionDepth()
        Returns:
        the depth of the note within the discussion. The root note of the discussion has depth 0. A reply on the root note note has depth 1, a reply on that reply depth 2 and so on.

      • getDiscussionId

        public Long getDiscussionId()
        Returns:
        the ID of the discussion the note belongs to

      • getDiscussionPath

        public String getDiscussionPath()
        Returns:
        The discussionPath separated with spaces instead of forward slashes, i.e. "12 34 56".

      • getLastDiscussionCreationDate

        public Date getLastDiscussionCreationDate()
        Returns:
        The date, the last note of this discussion was created.

      • getLastModificationDate

        public Date getLastModificationDate()
        Returns:
        the date of the last modification of the note. This value will equal the creation date if the note wasn't modified yet.

      • getNotifiedUsers

      • getNumberOfComments

        public int getNumberOfComments()
        Returns the number of replies to this note. This includes replies on replies and also replies that are direct messages which the current user might not be able to read.
        Returns:
        the number of replies

      • getNumberOfDiscussionNotes

        public int getNumberOfDiscussionNotes()
        Returns the number of notes in the discussion this note is part of. Notes the current user is not allowed to read, i.e. direct messages that were not sent to that user, are not included.
        Returns:
        the number of notes in the discussion

      • isCommentable

        public boolean isCommentable()
        Returns whether the current user can reply to this note. This is only possible if the current user has write access to the blog of the note and it is not a system note. Moreover, the author of the note must not have been anonymized.
        Returns:
        true if the current user can reply to this note

      • isDeletable

        public boolean isDeletable()
        Whether the current user can delete this note. Deleting is only possible if the current user is the manager of the blog or he is the author of the note and there are no comments to the note and it is not a direct message.
        Returns:
        true if the current user can delete this note, false otherwise
